DAT
id=qid::label=str::text=lstr::
24630::$$$message_0216_0000_0000$$$::                                            Winter, five years ago.::
24631::$$$message_0216_0001_0000$$$::It was a beautiful, moonlit night.[lr]::
24632::$$$message_0216_0001_0001$$$::I was just enjoying the sight with my father, Kiritsugu Emiya.[lr]::
24633::$$$message_0216_0001_0002$$$::It was winter, but it wasn't very cold.[lr]::
24634::$$$message_0216_0001_0003$$$::On the veranda it was just a little chilly, the perfect weather to watch the moon.::
24635::$$$message_0216_0002_0000$$$::Kiritsugu didn't go outside much anymore.[lr]::
24636::$$$message_0216_0002_0001$$$::He rarely went out, and he spent most of his time lounging around the house.[lr]::
24637::$$$message_0216_0002_0002$$$::...Every time I recall this, I still feel regret.[lr]::
24638::$$$message_0216_0002_0003$$$::Why didn't I realize that he was acting the way any creature does when they know their time is almost up?::
24639::$$$message_0216_0003_0000$$$::"When I was a boy, I wanted to be a champion of justice."[lr]::
24640::$$$message_0216_0003_0001$$$::He blurted it out, just out of nowhere.[lr]::
24641::$$$message_0216_0003_0002$$$::My father, who already seemed like a champion of justice in my eyes, said that as if he were reflecting on a memory.::
24642::$$$message_0216_0004_0000$$$::"What, you [font italic=true]wanted[font italic=false] to? So you gave up on it?"[lr]::
24643::$$$message_0216_0004_0001$$$::I asked, unable to completely hide my disappointment.[lr]::
24644::$$$message_0216_0004_0002$$$::Kiritsugu smiled apologetically, and looked up at the distant moon.::
24645::$$$message_0216_0005_0000$$$::"Unfortunately, yes. You can only be a hero for so long. It gets harder to call yourself one as you grow up. I wish I'd found that out earlier."[lr]::
24646::$$$message_0216_0005_0001$$$::That made sense to me.[lr]::
24647::$$$message_0216_0005_0002$$$::I wasn't sure why, but if Kiritsugu said it, then it had to be true.::
24648::$$$message_0216_0006_0000$$$::"Oh. Well, that's too bad."[lr]::
24649::$$$message_0216_0006_0001$$$::"Yes. It really is too bad."[lr]::
24650::$$$message_0216_0006_0002$$$::Kiritsugu nodded in agreement.[lr]::
24651::$$$message_0216_0006_0003$$$::So I just kind of blurted something out, as if it were a natural thing to say.::
24652::$$$message_0216_0007_0000$$$::"Okay. If you can't do it, then I'll do it for you.[lr]::
24653::$$$message_0216_0007_0001$$$::You can't do anything because you're an adult, but I can. You can leave your dream to me."::
24654::$$$message_0216_0008_0000$$$::[font italic=true]Because I'll make it a reality.[font italic=false]::
24655::$$$message_0216_0009_0000$$$::The bold promise made my father smile.[lr]::
24656::$$$message_0216_0009_0001$$$::His face said everything I needed to know.[lr]::
24657::$$$message_0216_0009_0002$$$::Kiritsugu made a long, contented sigh, and whispered,[lr]::
24658::$$$message_0216_0009_0003$$$::"Ah...that's a relief."[lr]::
24659::$$$message_0216_0009_0004$$$::There, he closed his eyes, and so too his life came to a close.::
24660::$$$message_0216_0010_0000$$$::He looked so peaceful, like he was just going to wake up in the morning, so I didn't think much about it.[lr]::
24661::$$$message_0216_0010_0001$$$::Maybe it was because by then I was used to seeing death.[lr]::
24662::$$$message_0216_0010_0002$$$::On a winter night, the man I called my father looked up at the moon and entered a long sleep.::
24663::$$$message_0216_0011_0000$$$::The yard was dead silent...not so much as a single chirp from an insect.[lr]::
24664::$$$message_0216_0011_0001$$$::I still remember how fiercely my eyes blazed on that bright, clear night.[lr]::
24665::$$$message_0216_0011_0002$$$::I didn't cry aloud, nor did I feel sad.[lr]::
24666::$$$message_0216_0011_0003$$$::But tears flowed down my cheek until the moon sank past the horizon.::
24667::$$$message_0216_0012_0000$$$::This happened in the winter, five years ago.[lr]::
24668::$$$message_0216_0012_0001$$$::I probably cried ten years' worth of tears in that time, so after that, there was nothing left.::
24669::$$$message_0216_0013_0000$$$::Fuji-nee's dad took care of the funeral arrangements, and that's how I ended up living in the Emiya mansion all alone.[lr]::
24670::$$$message_0216_0013_0001$$$::Kiritsugu's passing didn't change anything for me.[lr]::
24671::$$$message_0216_0013_0002$$$::I was set on becoming a man who champions justice and does what's right, just like my father, so I didn't have time to sit around.::
24672::$$$message_0216_0014_0000$$$::    That's right.[lr]::
24673::$$$message_0216_0014_0001$$$::I never talk about this, but I still remember it.[lr]::
24674::$$$message_0216_0014_0002$$$::Ten years ago, a man saved me from a fire.[lr]::
24675::$$$message_0216_0014_0003$$$::He picked up a burned, dying child and carried him out of hell, weeping with joy.::
24676::$$$message_0216_0015_0000$$$::I've admired him ever since.[lr]::
24677::$$$message_0216_0015_0001$$$::Nobody saved me.[lr]::
24678::$$$message_0216_0015_0002$$$::I couldn't save anyone.[lr]::
24679::$$$message_0216_0015_0003$$$::In the ruins of the fire, there was only a boy who was saved, and the man who saved him.[lr]::
24680::$$$message_0216_0015_0004$$$::   That's why I aspired to be like him.::
24681::$$$message_0216_0016_0000$$$::I wanted to become a hero of justice that saves people and doesn't let anyone die.[lr]::
24682::$$$message_0216_0016_0001$$$::That's who he wanted to be, and he passed his wish on to me before quietly letting the curtain fall.::
24683::$$$message_0216_0017_0000$$$::It's only natural for a child to follow in their father's footsteps.[lr]::
24684::$$$message_0216_0017_0001$$$::Shirou Emiya must become a hero of justice and save someone the same way that he was once saved.[lr]::
24685::$$$message_0216_0017_0002$$$::I swore to myself I would do it.[lr]::
24686::$$$message_0216_0017_0003$$$::I vowed to fulfill the dream of the man I most admired.::
24687::$$$message_0216_0018_0000$$$::...But honestly, I didn't know how.[lr]::
24688::$$$message_0216_0018_0001$$$::What did Kiritsugu mean by doing the right thing and championing justice? How can I grow up faster? Is there some magical way to make Kiritsugu's dream of 'making everyone happy' come true? Seriously, what am I supposed do when I become a Master and I can't get the blonde girl with me out of my head[line2]::
24689::$$$message_0216_0019_0000$$$::"...rgh."[lr]::
24690::$$$message_0216_0019_0001$$$::I wake up in my room.[lr]::
24691::$$$message_0216_0019_0002$$$::"...Ugh...something tastes...terrible..."[lr]::
24692::$$$message_0216_0019_0003$$$::The steely tang of blood clouds my mouth.[lr]::
24693::$$$message_0216_0019_0004$$$::It pooled in my mouth while I slept, and every time I breathed, heavy, metallic air filled my lungs.::
24694::$$$message_0216_0020_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
24695::$$$message_0216_0020_0001$$$::I'm not sure why I feel this way.[lr]::
24696::$$$message_0216_0020_0002$$$::A violent urge to vomit makes me want to go wash my face in the restroom.::
24697::$$$message_0216_0021_0000$$$::"Okay."[lr]::
24698::$$$message_0216_0021_0001$$$::I lift myself out of bed.[lr]::
24699::$$$message_0216_0021_0002$$$::Dizziness sets my head spinning.[lr]::
24700::$$$message_0216_0021_0003$$$::Feeling uneasy on my feet, I plant a hand on the wall.[lr]::
24701::$$$message_0216_0021_0004$$$::"...Ugh."[lr]::
24702::$$$message_0216_0021_0005$$$::I try to move, but it only makes the nausea worse.[lr]::
24703::$$$message_0216_0021_0006$$$::...No, it's more pain than nausea.::
24704::$$$message_0216_0022_0000$$$::My body feels sluggish, and my insides seem to churn whenever I move. I imagine this is about what it'd feel like if someone forced hot lead down my throat.[lr]::
24705::$$$message_0216_0022_0001$$$::"Ugh...imagining that is making me feel like I'm going to run a fever."[lr]::
24706::$$$message_0216_0022_0002$$$::I wipe the sweat from my forehead, and hobble out my room, leaning against the wall.::
24707::$$$message_0216_0023_0000$$$::"Okay, I feel a little better."[lr]::
24708::$$$message_0216_0023_0001$$$::I wash my face and dry off my sweat-drenched body.[lr]::
24709::$$$message_0216_0023_0002$$$::"...Huh?"[lr]::
24710::$$$message_0216_0023_0003$$$::For some reason, my abdomen is wrapped in bandages.[lr]::
24711::$$$message_0216_0023_0004$$$::I have no idea why, but I'll deal with it later.::
24712::$$$message_0216_0024_0000$$$::"...I'm hungry. Did I leave any extra food in the fridge...?"[lr]::
24713::$$$message_0216_0024_0001$$$::My stomach still feels like it's churning, but my body needs nourishment.::
24714::$$$message_0216_0025_0000$$$::"Kngh..."[lr]::
24715::$$$message_0216_0025_0001$$$::I suck up the discomfort and keep walking, braced against the wall.[lr]::
24716::$$$message_0216_0025_0002$$$::The dizziness won't go away, and worst of all, my whole body feels dull.[lr]::
24717::$$$message_0216_0025_0003$$$::"Ow! Ow, ow..."[lr]::
24718::$$$message_0216_0025_0004$$$::I keep moving forward, making pathetic noises along the way.[lr]::
24719::$$$message_0216_0025_0005$$$::What the hell did I do before I went to bed last night?[lr]::
24720::$$$message_0216_0025_0006$$$::I don't remember training strenuously enough to make my entire body ache.::
24721::$$$message_0216_0026_0000$$$::I reach the living room.[lr]::
24722::$$$message_0216_0026_0001$$$::Sakura and Fuji-nee must be at school.[lr]::
24723::$$$message_0216_0026_0002$$$::There's no signs of breakfast, nor do I see any remnants of Fuji-nee wrecking the place.[lr]::
24724::$$$message_0216_0026_0003$$$::The living room's quiet, like a typical Sunday[line2][lr]::
24725::$$$message_0216_0026_0004$$$::"Morning. Sorry I came in without asking, Emiya."[lr]::
24726::$$$message_0216_0026_0005$$$::...or not.::
24727::$$$message_0216_0027_0000$$$::"Wha... Eh!?"[lr]::
24728::$$$message_0216_0027_0001$$$::Rin Tohsaka is sitting on the floor by the table in the living room.[lr]::
24729::$$$message_0216_0027_0002$$$::She's so calm, like she owns the place. So much so that [font italic=true]I[font italic=false] feel like the guest here.::
24730::$$$message_0216_0028_0000$$$::"..."[lr]::
24731::$$$message_0216_0028_0001$$$::I have no idea what to say, so I plop down on a cushion.[lr]::
24732::$$$message_0216_0028_0002$$$::And then I take a deep breath.::
24733::$$$message_0216_0029_0000$$$::"Tohsaka, why're you[line2]"[lr]::
24734::$$$message_0216_0029_0001$$$::"Stop. Shouldn't you apologize to me first? I can't move on from last night until you say sorry for what you did."[lr]::
24735::$$$message_0216_0029_0002$$$::...I can't even finish asking why she's in my house.::
24736::$$$message_0216_0030_0000$$$::Tohsaka's glare is all I need to know how angry she is.[lr]::
24737::$$$message_0216_0030_0001$$$::She seems upset about something that happened last night, but what exactly...::
24738::$$$message_0216_0031_0000$$$::"Wait."[lr]::
24739::$$$message_0216_0031_0001$$$::I remember now.[lr]::
24740::$$$message_0216_0031_0002$$$::Right, this isn't the time for me to be leisurely breathing in the morning air.[lr]::
24741::$$$message_0216_0031_0003$$$::I tried to help Saber, and... Berserker gutted me like a fish.::
24742::$$$message_0216_0032_0000$$$::"Ugh..."[lr]::
24743::$$$message_0216_0032_0001$$$::The nausea returns.[lr]::
24744::$$$message_0216_0032_0002$$$::A chill grips my entire body as I remember the feeling of having a gaping hole in my body.::
24745::$$$message_0216_0033_0000$$$::Wait, that's weird.[lr]::
24746::$$$message_0216_0033_0001$$$::I should've died instantly.::
24747::$$$message_0216_0034_0000$$$::"That's weird. Why am I still here?"[lr]::
24748::$$$message_0216_0034_0001$$$::"Do you remember now? You did something damned stupid last night. I hope you regret it."::
24749::$$$message_0216_0035_0000$$$::Tohsaka huffs critically.[lr]::
24750::$$$message_0216_0035_0001$$$::That kinda ticks me off.[lr]::
24751::$$$message_0216_0035_0002$$$::My brain, frozen since seeing Tohsaka in my living room, finally grinds into action.::
24752::$$$message_0216_0036_0000$$$::"What are you talking about? I had no choice. Well, sure...it might seem like an idiotic move if you just look at the results...and I definitely meant for it to go better than it did...[lr]::
24753::$$$message_0216_0036_0001$$$::So I wouldn't say it was a mistake."[lr]::
24754::$$$message_0216_0036_0002$$$::I return her glare, insisting that I'm not an idiot.::
24755::$$$message_0216_0037_0000$$$::"...Mrgh."[lr]::
24756::$$$message_0216_0037_0001$$$::Wh-what?[lr]::
24757::$$$message_0216_0037_0002$$$::Why is she making such a show of sighing at me? ::
24758::$$$message_0216_0038_0000$$$::"If the Master dies, the Servant disappears too, remember? I can't believe you actually tried to shield your own Servant."::
24759::$$$message_0216_0039_0000$$$::"Listen. If you die, then Saber is gone, too. If you wanted to save Saber, you should have thought of another way to do it from a safe distance.[lr]::
24760::$$$message_0216_0039_0001$$$::...Honestly, do you realize how pointless it is to risk your own life for your Servant's?"::
24761::$$$message_0216_0040_0000$$$::"I wasn't shielding her. I was just trying to get her out of there. I didn't think that would happen to me."[lr]::
24762::$$$message_0216_0040_0001$$$::I knew I might die if I got near a monster like that, but that's beside the point.::
24763::$$$message_0216_0041_0000$$$::"...Fine. Then you had the wrong idea."[lr]::
24764::$$$message_0216_0041_0001$$$::Tohsaka only looks more irritated, like she knows exactly what I'm thinking.::
24765::$$$message_0216_0042_0000$$$::"I'll be straight with you, Emiya. I didn't take you to the church so that you could win.[lr]::
24766::$$$message_0216_0042_0001$$$::I was just trying to give you a chance to survive because you literally don't know anything. It sounds like you still don't get it."::
24767::$$$message_0216_0043_0000$$$::"A chance to survive?"[lr]::
24768::$$$message_0216_0043_0001$$$::"Yeah. I figured you wouldn't take risks or really do much if you knew defeat meant death. But it looks like you're the kind of person to walk out at night even in a situation like this.[lr]::
24769::$$$message_0216_0043_0002$$$::I thought that if I scared you straight, you wouldn't throw your own life away for someone else, and if you're lucky, you'd make it until the end."::
24770::$$$message_0216_0044_0000$$$::"I see. That didn't cross my mind."::
24771::$$$message_0216_0045_0000$$$::"But why are you upset? What does me dying have to do with you?"::
24772::$$$message_0216_0046_0000$$$::"It has everything to do with me, because you made me worry all night long!"::
24773::$$$message_0216_0047_0000$$$::Tohsaka is practically throwing a tantrum.[lr]::
24774::$$$message_0216_0047_0001$$$::...But, okay.[lr]::
24775::$$$message_0216_0047_0002$$$::It actually feels good to have someone worry about me.[lr]::
24776::$$$message_0216_0047_0003$$$::From her tone, it sounds like Tohsaka was the one who took care of me.::
24777::$$$message_0216_0048_0000$$$::"Is that so? Guess I owe you one, Tohsaka. Thanks."[lr]::
24778::$$$message_0216_0048_0001$$$::I bow my head in appreciation and apology.[lr]::
24779::$$$message_0216_0048_0002$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false]::
24780::$$$message_0216_0049_0000$$$::"Hmph! As long as you understand. If you've learned your lesson, then use your head next time."::
24781::$$$message_0216_0050_0000$$$::Tohsaka quickly turns away.[lr]::
24782::$$$message_0216_0050_0001$$$::She might still be edgy, but I feel like she's in a better mood.::
24783::$$$message_0216_0051_0000$$$::"Then we're done with what happened last night.[lr]::
24784::$$$message_0216_0051_0001$$$::Let's get down to it, then. Do you want to talk business, or talk about yesterday?"::
24785::$$$message_0216_0052_0000$$$::"Hm?"[lr]::
24786::$$$message_0216_0052_0001$$$::Tohsaka prompts me matter-of-factly.[lr]::
24787::$$$message_0216_0052_0002$$$::Her straightforwardness takes me off guard, but now that I think about it, she must be here only because she has something to discuss.::
24788::$$$message_0216_0053_0000$$$::If she hadn't had something to discuss, she'd have gone home already.[lr]::
24789::$$$message_0216_0053_0001$$$::Tohsaka's my enemy, so what could she have to talk about that would prompt her to stay in enemy territory?::
24790::$$$message_0216_0054_0000$$$::I'm curious to know what she's thinking, and I also want to know what else happened last night.[lr]::
24791::$$$message_0216_0054_0001$$$::I have to ask anyway, so...[lr]::

